        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName> <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Novr. 5611</date></p>
			<p>My dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">A few days ago I received your letter of<lb/> the <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August</date> last&#44; the detention of which has been owing to<lb/> some accident having happened to the &#8220;<placeName>Kingston</placeName>&#8221; which necessitated<lb/> her putting back. By the same opportunity&#44; I believe&#44; the intermediate<lb/> Nos. of the Occident have arrived&#44; tho I have not yet received them.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I regret to inform you that the Cholera<lb/> has been raging with unusual malignity in this <placeName>Island</placeName> for the<lb/> last six weeks&#44; to which fearful malady my lamented father<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> fell a victim on <date>Tuesday Evening last the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst. As the<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> is but just up&#44; I have been unable to attend to anything<lb/> hence my non&#45;receipt of the Occidents just arrived. I have handed<lb/> over the names of the subscribers to this valuable periodical to <persName>Mr Lawton</persName><lb/> your agent&#44; whose <add>&#63;</add> will enable him to attend to the pecuniary<lb/> part with success. Notwithstanding this&#44; be assured I will not<lb/> slacken in my endeavors to obtain further subscribers thereto&#44; as well<lb/> as to your partnered<add>&#63;</add> publication of the &#8220;Jewish Advocate.&#8221; Still&#44; it is<lb/> my duty to tell you candidly&#44; I do not apprehend any degree of success&#44;<lb/> as the distress of our Community is beyond expression. For some time<lb/> &#40;indeed since the appearance of the Cholera amongst us&#41; Business has<lb/> been at a complete stand&#44; and the means of the <hi rend="underline">few</hi> who are blessed</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>with worldly substance have been largely called on for the<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> of their own as well as the <hi rend="underline">General</hi> poor of the City. Large<lb/> Collections have been made both in the Synagogue as well as out<lb/> of doors. Notwithstanding&#44; the great mass of our people are materially<lb/> altered in circumstances&#44; so much so&#44; that I fear the pecuniary<lb/> position of our synagogues will be much affected thereby.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">A Day of General Humiliation was appointed<lb/> and observed on <date>Friday the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Nov.</date> last&#44; but owing to the<lb/> inclemency of the weather which prevented a great majority from<lb/> attending&#44; the Governor appointed <date>Wednesday the 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> following for a<lb/> similar purpose. I need scarcely add lost days were religiously<lb/> observed by our people.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">There seems to be a desire manifested in<lb/> <placeName>Falmouth</placeName> for the establishment of a regular congregation&#44; and the erection<lb/> of a synagogue&#44; but I fear&#44; that internal dissensions&#44; chiefly relative<lb/> to <add>Hebrew</add> are obstanly<add>&#63;</add> to so desirable an end. Perhaps a few<lb/> remarks from your pen in the Occident might be serviceable.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I forgot to state that a &#8220;Hebrew Benevolent<lb/> Society&#8221; has been formed for the relief of our destitute Brethren<lb/> during the prevalence of the Cholera. It is to be hoped that when the<lb/> Almighty shall have&#44; in His mercy&#44; removed from us this &#8220;noisome<lb/> pestilence&#44;&#8221; the association will not be suffered to fall to the ground.</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>Our friend <persName>B A Franklin</persName> takes a very active part in its<lb/> management.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I duly forwarded your letter to the <persName>Reverend<lb/> A P Mendes</persName>&#44; thro his father.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With the assurance of my esteem and good wishes&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me&#44; my dear sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Yours very faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Jacobs</persName>.</p>
          
        </body>
